###  https://sakuna.ph/Wildfire
:Wildfire rdf:type owl:Class ;
          rdfs:subClassOf :Climatological ;
          rdfs:label "Wildfire"@en ;
          skos:definition "Any uncontrolled and non-prescribed combustion or burning of plants in a natural setting such as a forest, grassland, brush land or tundra, which consumes natural fuels and spreads based on environmental conditions (e.g., wind, or topography). Wildfires can be triggered by lightning or human actions." .


###  https://sakuna.ph/WildfireGeneral
:WildfireGeneral rdf:type owl:Class ;
                 rdfs:subClassOf :Wildfire ;
                 rdfs:label "Wildfire (General)"@en ;
                 skos:definition "Wildfire (general): Any type of fire  in a natural setting such as a grassland, mountain, brush land or tundra, which consumes natural fuels such as tress and spreads based on environmental conditions (e.g., wind, or topography). Wildfires can be triggered by lightning or human actions. Can affect animals, trees, and properties. Can be due to El Nino." .


